<Content>Too noisy The location is excellent for getting around the central city on foot. The desk staff was friendly. Rooms were small but adequate. The rooms and lobby were clean. Noise was a huge issue. This is a very young area, with hostels, bars and restaurants, and night-owls. Street noise kept us from sleeping soundly until about 3 am, and it seemed that as soon as the partying stopped, the city sanitation (garbage) crews were out. Closed windows barely muffled the noise, and even earplugs didn't work.We also got a lot of noise from the hallway and adjacent rooms. The cleaning staff's station was right outside our door, so starting at about 8 am and lasting until we left for the day, we heard the banging of brooms and mops and the rustling of plastic laundry bags.All in all, it was almost impossible to get more than 4 - 5 hours of sleep each night. I'd say that while the biggest advantage of the hotel is its location, that is also its biggest disadvantage because of the constant noise. 
